body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello! Thank you for contacting Lee's Auto Solutions. My name is Bobby Lee. May I have your name please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hi Bobby, my name is Natalie Morgan.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Natalie. How can I assist you today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I have a question about my recent service at your dealership.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Sure, I'll do my best to help. Could you please provide me with your customer ID and phone number for verification purposes?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Yes. My customer ID is two three five six and my phone number is five five five eight seven six nine

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for the information, Natalie. Is there anything else I can assist you with?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all. Thank you for your help, Bobby.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Natalie. Thank you for contacting Lee's Auto Solutions. Have a great day!
